but it was general enough not to have to worry. I think that from what I've read with issues that

00:18:19.599 --> 00:18:23.920
have been opened up over the years, there's a format that Word likes to use called OpenXML,

00:18:23.920 --> 00:18:28.479
which is maybe not really that open. And that just doesn't seem to play very well with Cordo

00:18:28.479 --> 00:18:33.920
at this time. Or maybe Pandoc. It just doesn't play very well with it. Great. Time for one last

00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:38.959
question. How do people typically consume these reports? Is it with your guidance, or is it they

00:18:38.959 --> 00:18:47.199
read through on their own? Most of the time, they just want them. So I'm not under the impression

00:18:47.199 --> 00:18:53.359
that... Well, there is their importance. They need to reference them in their larger documents. So we

00:18:53.359 --> 00:18:58.160
have what we call dossiers in the pharmaceutical industry that we need when we're asking for a new

00:18:58.160 --> 00:19:02.239
treatment to be approved or we're making manufacturing change where I go in. We have

00:19:02.239 --> 00:19:07.199
these communications. So a lot of times, they need these reports because they want to reference them,

00:19:07.199 --> 00:19:11.119
and somebody reviewing them at the health authority agencies will want to see that.

00:19:11.680 --> 00:19:18.800
So I doubt... Some of them do read them end to end. So of course, that's a whole other... If I

00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:22.719
understand the question correctly, that's a whole other topic to try to make them as readable as

00:19:22.719 --> 00:19:29.839
possible. But this helps me. I go back to when I was... You could tell by my age. When I was first

00:19:29.839 --> 00:19:35.199
writing my dissertation, LaTeX just became available. And I thought that was the coolest

00:19:35.199 --> 00:19:40.160
thing. And I'm so glad that after 20 years of having to muck around in Word documents, maybe

00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:44.479
the last 10 years or so or five years, I've been able to actually use markup language to create the

00:19:44.479 --> 00:19:49.439
documents. So I don't have a good answer to that. I mean, it just depends on the context whether

00:19:49.439 --> 00:19:59.280
they want to review it or not. Thank you, Bill. Yeah. Thank you, everyone.

